Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Stones throw from the Market Square
Flexible tenure with healthy rent return

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
96-100 Grote Street is a key part of the Chinatown Precinct in SA located directly opposite the Lions at the northern end of Moonta Street. With constantly active nightlife, plentiful street parking, and access to the main thoroughfares through the Adelaide CBD there is a lot on offer here for investors looking to secure a significant Adelaide holding.

This 767sqm* space is tenanted by Tangritah Uyghur Restaurant and Star Academy Dance Studio paying $159,457* net per annum. With strong holding income already in place 96-100 Grote Street is an ideal investment for groups looking for future flexibility.  

With the upcoming Market Square redevelopment just across the road, there will be a huge uplift to the local area with a modern quality office space, retail market ‘hub’ and a hotel and apartment offering all in the one spot. The $400,000,000 price tag will be sure to have run-on affects to the immediate area and we expect 96-100 Grote Street will see benefit. 

Key investment highlights include:
- Multi tenanted Chinatown investment
- Estimated net rental of $159,457*
- 1,450sqm* corner site 
- 8* on site car parks
- Capital City zoning for 53meters
- Perfectly positioned near the planned ‘Market Square’ redevelopment
- Expansion opportunities in current tenancy mix

For sale via Expressions of Interest closing at 4:00pm on the 30th of September 

Harry Einarson
Ned Looker 
Jing Jun (JJ) Heng

CBRE are proud to present Suite 502, 147 Pirie Street to market for sale available via Private Treaty. This prime positioned, premium strata suite is situated on the 5th floor of the Aurora building and benefits from the fantastic views over Hindmarsh Square. Located in the heart of the CBD the suite is perfectly positioned for businesses with public transport, Grenfell Street and Rundle Mall within walking distance.  The added bonus is the amenities the building provides including a roof top pool, fully equipped gym, client function centre, a ground floor café and full building concierge.

Key Investment Highlights Include:

- Premium CBD strata in the heart of the CBD
- Magnificent views to Hindmarsh Square
- Flexible 45sqm suite with the flexibility of dividing 
- Impressive of amenities throughout including in-building gym, pool, and café

FOR SALE VIA PRIVATE TREATY - $280,000 PLUS GST

With 80% of people in Adelaide driving to work and one of the most accessible car parks in the Adelaide CBD, 225 North Terrace is perfectly located to provide convenient parking for shopping, dining, business, universities, cultural experiences and entertainment seekers.

- 97% leased with long term leases to anchor tenants Wilson Parking Australia and David Jones Limited.
- $7.495M pa estimated fully leased net income.
- 4.43-year WALE by gross income with owner option renewal.
- 1,206 car parking bays.
- Basement, ground and first floor retail accommodation of some 4,180sqm within the Charles Street Plaza.
- Only 50 metres (approx.) from Rundle Mall.

For Sale by Expressions of Interest closing 4pm (ACDT) Thursday 3 December 2020

As any Adelaidian would know the iconic building at 221-225 Flinders Street, Adelaide has been the home of one of Adelaide’s most recognizable businesses in The South Australian German Club. This multiple story building has been utilised as a function hall/restaurant/bar in its 105 years of occupancy with the existing improvements being constructed in 1970. 

The property presents the below characteristics sure to appeal to the astute owner occupier, investor or developer:

- Functional and prominent improvements of 2,311sqm* gross  building area
- Three story building with basement and mixture of lift and stair access throughout
- 16.15m* frontage to Flinders and Ifould Streets
- 943sqm* site area
- Flexible Capital City Zoning allowing up to 53m*
- Offered with vacant possession therefore ready for refurbishment, redevelopment (STCC) or occupation*

For Sale by Expressions of Interest closing Thursday 8th of November at 2:00pm
